text:
I’m working for you. Follow my progress by subscribing to my monthly newsletter or joining me on one of these social platforms:
https://t.co/7QcUPonDeO
https://t.co/6Vxu89xlep
https://t.co/GtHLHIxs0D
https://t.co/KPADue5YWu
#NationalSTEAMDay @CEE1983

It’s National STEAM Day! STEAM education is about creative, critical thinking that prepares students for successful careers. 

With STEAM education we can continue to put Oregon and the country at the forefront of innovative scientific and technological advancements.
I’m excited to see this new venture educate and support future workers in behavior health who will provide essential support for older adults across the state.

The new Oregon Center of Excellence for Behavioral Health and Aging is an innovative partnership between @PortlandState and @OHSUNews to support behavioral health care for older adults. https://t.co/Ut2SqW9I4Q

The newly renovated Vernier Science Center at @Portland_State is full of state-of-the-art equipment and lab spaces that were designed around the needs of PSU’s diverse student body. I appreciated learning more about the Center from school leaders, faculty, & students. https://t.co/e2s1pfTTdL
This #NationalFamilyCaregiversMonth, I’m committed to working with my @DemWomenCaucus colleagues to advocate for policies and resources that support caregivers and their families.

1 in 5 Americans is a caregiver, but their work is often unpaid and overlooked. 

Many struggle to keep up with full time jobs in addition to providing care for a loved one.
https://t.co/tA8bw2TZL2
https://t.co/QTaypbACgg
https://t.co/apld0J8uWF

I came to Congress to help improve lives and to advocate for the interests and values of Oregonians. 

That’s true whether I serve in the majority or the minority and no matter who holds the presidency.

This more than $10 million in funding for the Tualatin Mountain Forest project from the climate bill we passed will help preserve critical habitat, increase water quality, and add new local recreational opportunities for Oregonians living in or visiting the Portland metro area.

In my visit to the Multnomah Channel Marsh restoration site, I heard more about how the project is part of a larger effort to protect and rehabilitate an important watershed that stretches across Portland’s West Hills.

https://t.co/tOlgOaPmpp

For low-income families, paying school lunch account processing fees takes away money that could be used to put food on the table. This new USDA policy will help lower costs for millions of families in Oregon and across the country.

Oregon: tomorrow is your last chance to submit ballots for this election. Ballots must be received or mailed with a valid post​mark by 8 p.m. on Election Day, Tuesday, November 5th.​​​​​​​​​

To find an official drop box location near you, visit: https://t.co/C6kZrMB7Tb
The important basic research they do at Vollum shows great promise in areas like developing cures for Alzheimer’s, MS, Parkinson’s, and other neurological disorders.
I appreciated learning more about the fascinating neuroscience work happening at the Vollum Institute on the OHSU campus. https://t.co/VO81TNjozt
With the OBCC, those in need of behavioral health care will spend less time waiting in emergency rooms and more time getting the care they need.

I enthusiastically supported funding for OHSU’s new Oregon Behavioral Health Coordination Center, which provides real-time information about where behavioral health beds are available in the metro region and across the state. https://t.co/sl6W3B4POy

Oregon is receiving $37.5 million & Oregon Tribal nations are receiving $5.4 million in funding to help low-income households pay their heating bills this winter. I’m glad to have supported the increase in Low Income Home Energy Assistance Program funding in the last budget bill.

Congratulations to OHSU’s Dr. Haijao Zhang and Dr. Ramon Barajas Jr. for being selected as Biden Cancer Moonshot awardees! I deeply appreciate the work of these doctors and other researchers working to end cancer. 
https://t.co/d0HZ7ZMhDF

It is heartbreaking that abortion bans and restrictions are causing preventable deaths and life-changing health conditions. 

We must restore full reproductive rights in our country to save lives.
We also discussed the need to address privacy rights of patients and the proliferation of misinformation regarding abortion care.

I joined @RonWyden, @PPCW leaders, and local doctors for a roundtable discussion about the ongoing harmful consequences from having politicians - rather than patients and health care providers – make health care decisions.
It’s been more than 2 years since the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade, and we have seen many devastating cases of patients denied life-saving care. https://t.co/dtWX09kn1S

During Native American Heritage Month we celebrate the diverse cultures, histories, and traditions of American Indians, Alaska Natives, and Native Hawaiians and recognize their vast contributions to our country.
Día de los Muertos is a time to remember lost loved ones and honor their memories. I wish a meaningful holiday to those observing.

The local Scouts I met with in Beaverton had lots of good questions about how laws are passed, voting, and my experience as an elected official. I hope they have a great time completing the rest of the “My Community” Adventure! https://t.co/xDaiiuZJSH
Best wishes for a bright and joyful Festival of Lights to all who celebrate Diwali!
Happy Halloween! I hope everyone celebrating has a fun and safe evening.
My Coastal Restoration Act would support projects like this, which provide critical habitat for fish and wildlife and help store climate-warming carbon.
It was a beautiful fall day to learn more about how Metro and the Lower Columbia Estuary Partnership are working together to restore natural wetlands near Sauvie Island. https://t.co/oNnmhlt9es

It was exciting to hear about plans for the James Beard Public Market, which will help reinvigorate downtown Portland and create opportunities for local chefs, producers, and entrepreneurs to showcase the bounty of Oregon’s culinary scene.
Portland is a great food city that’s about to get even better. https://t.co/yXSVdPqmXs
Before the roundtable discussion, I also visited some of the classrooms at St. James. Thank you to the staff and kids of Fireflies Class for hosting us for story time! https://t.co/xhbB1Lqryl

Thank you to local child care leaders at St. James Child Development Center for joining @jvegapederson & me at a roundtable discussion about how the government can expand access to affordable child care & make the care industry more sustainable for providers and their staff.
Lowering the cost of child care helps children and families and also benefits the economy. https://t.co/DrqvksHCjR
I will continue working with my colleagues to #StopProject2025

House Republicans have spent much of this Congress targeting the LGBTQI+ community with discriminatory bills. Read the @EqualityCaucus's new report to learn more about how the GOP is attempting to advance #Project2025's anti-equality agenda. 
 https://t.co/QlxkVjA3Ju
It’s important to preserve and rehabilitate affordable housing we currently have, and I’m grateful to have helped secure $2 million in federal funding for this project.
lt was great to celebrate the reopening of Fairfield Apartments with the many Oregonians involved in its renovation. https://t.co/pJLIAsewWs

Our student loan system should not punish borrowers who experience significant hardship. This proposed rule would give these borrowers much needed relief and keep them out of further financial distress.

The President’s apology and the Department of Interior’s report are good first steps toward healing the harm inflicted by the Indian boarding school system and providing true justice for the Native communities still affected by forced assimilation policies.
Thank you to President Biden for acknowledging the pain and offering a sincere apology for that ugly part of U.S. history.
I appreciate Secretary Haaland for commissioning the investigation that revealed the scope of the injury and the depth of the harm among families and Tribal members.

Over the years Indian boarding schools caused significant trauma and even death to Native children.
 https://t.co/4kuvkVYZ29

I helped secure a grant so the hospital can build a vertical evacuation tower that will keep patients, providers, & other community members safe in the event of an earthquake or tsunami. This project will transform healthcare on the coast & will be a model for other development.
It was exciting to celebrate the expansion of Columbia Memorial Hospital in Astoria, bolstered by a $20 million federal investment. https://t.co/Ryb7aG06Q2

Investing in clean energy can cut costs for local businesses while benefitting communities and the planet. I was able to see the massive new rooftop solar array at Fort George Brewery, which was installed with help from a $1 million USDA grant. https://t.co/PdJ0QrMOf3
I enjoyed hearing from students about the books they like to read and what stories interest them. Some politicians are banning books; we are delivering them!

It was exciting to deliver several books I picked out from the Library of Congress to Markham Elementary and Robert Gray Middle School with @PPSConnect Superintendent Dr. Armstrong. https://t.co/5uOC6oxKwp

Arts and culture must be part of our efforts to build healthy and thriving communities in Portland and across the state. It was inspiring to hear from the Portland’5 Youth Advisory Council about their work and vision for the arts. They give me hope for the future! https://t.co/yfiyG26Bcz

I visited @UOregon's Ballmer Institute to learn more about their innovative approach to expanding opportunities for students to prepare to work in this important field and for educators to learn more about how to address the complex needs of their students.
We must invest in a workforce that can meet the mental and behavioral health needs of children and youth. https://t.co/CYrWG03rMg

I enjoyed meeting with members of Beaverton Mayor’s Youth Advisory Board and speaking more about my work in Congress. The students had lots of great questions, and I’m excited to see what these young civic leaders accomplish! https://t.co/4H90Oem6Y0
Happy Birthday, @SenJeffMerkley! https://t.co/fULIlwXyu4
I enthusiastically support this expansion because it will support local farmers and producers and help food insecure Oregonians purchase fresh produce.

Great news: The Farmers Market Fund is receiving funding from USDA to expand Oregon’s successful Double Up Food Bucks program. 
https://t.co/xnXFJHAVRJ
I look forward to working with the VA and my colleagues on both sides of the aisle to improve the transition into higher education and civilian life.

Returning veterans often face challenges when they come home. We have an obligation to take care of those who served and sacrificed for our country, and I met with student veterans and veteran service coordinators to learn more about their experiences in NW Oregon. https://t.co/w8cqJqCp3H

Republicans have thrown the student loan system into chaos trying to stop overdue student relief. This pause will be a lifeline for borrowers struggling to navigate their options and make the best decisions for themselves and their families.

I applaud the Biden-Harris Administration for pausing student loan payments for borrowers enrolled in the SAVE plan, an affordable option with meaningful consumer protections.
https://t.co/uyg11gx6IO[…]for-8-million-save-plan-borrowers/ar-AA1sF54o?ocid=BingNewsVerp
As I said during the discussion, “it’s hard to be optimistic about the future when you don’t have a place to call home.” Safe and stable housing is fundamental for individuals and families to thrive.

The affordable housing and homelessness crisis is affecting communities across the country. I was glad to join @BPC_Bipartisan for a conversation about how federal investments and policies can help address housing needs.
After receiving more than 16,000 complaints, the @FTC now has a rule advanced by the Biden-Harris administration that will make it as easy to cancel a subscription as it was to sign up.
Many people find that it’s very easy to sign up for a subscription, but difficult or impossible to cancel. Those days are over!

It was exciting to join @trimet and my good friend Rep. Blumenauer to celebrate a $25 million investment from the bipartisan infrastructure bill to help transform the Columbia Operations Facility into a clean bus maintenance and charging hub.
Expanding clean public transit is a key part of addressing the climate crisis and building healthier, more livable neighborhoods. https://t.co/g7QA9mRcv4

It was great to help celebrate the incredible work of Neighborhood House to support children, families, and seniors. Neighbor House and their dedicated staff create a better future by providing services people need to get ahead. https://t.co/coPaWCkDde
The improvements funded by the climate bill will help prevent these types of events so residents have a safe and stable place to call home.

On a tour of Powell Apartments, I heard more about how water damage caused by the ice storm earlier this year displaced some residents—including Michelle, who only recently moved back to her unit after extensive renovations.

It was great to join representatives from REACH CDC and @HUDgov’s Oregon Field Office to celebrate a new financial award that will help improve energy efficiency, lower energy costs for residents, and make the Powell and Admiral Apartments more resilient in extreme weather. https://t.co/KgA4ISVcAj

Thanks to the Inflation Reduction Act, seniors on Medicare can save more on prescription drugs and other healthcare costs. You can now visit https://t.co/j6G772jyRq to find the right coverage for you during Open Enrollment.

Lilly Ledbetter was a champion for equal pay, and women across the country have stronger protections against discrimination because of her advocacy. We can honor Lilly’s legacy by continuing her work to end the wage gap—starting with passing the Paycheck Fairness Act.

Congratulations to @Portland_State and @PortlandCC for signing a new Memorandum of Understanding that will improve pathways and opportunities for students interested in entering Oregon’s thriving semiconductor industry. I’m excited to see the results of this expanded partnership! https://t.co/EWKIuj2ezT

I am thankful for the Biden-Harris administration’s work to strengthen partnerships with Tribal governments—including on the restoration of the Columbia River Basin—and to document the harms of the Federal Indian Boarding School Initiative.
On Indigenous Peoples’ Day we uplift the perspectives of Native communities and recognize the historic injustices inflicted by the U.S. government, many of which are still felt today.
Wishing all who observe an easy fast and a meaningful Yom Kippur.
As the Co-Chair of the bipartisan Career and Technical Education (CTE) Caucus, it was exciting to also learn more about future plans for a CTE Skills Center in the former K-8 school.

I got to visit Nestucca Valley K-8 in southern Tillamook County. The beautiful new K-8 campus has softball and baseball fields, mountain bike trails, and a community playground. It’s also the largest seismically resilient building in South Tillamook County. https://t.co/ijXGwm8jCt
Neah-Kah-Nie High School is new to the district I represent, and it was wonderful to speak with student leaders, tour a construction class, and hear more about their onsite health clinic.
As a member of @EdWorkforceDems, I always appreciate visiting schools and meeting with educators and students. https://t.co/GI19AljZez
Washington County is a significant part of the district I represent, and it’s one of the most diverse and rapidly growing counties in Oregon.

I appreciated the opportunity to hear from several Washington County mayors about the challenges they face and how the federal government can partner on issues like housing. child care, and infrastructure. https://t.co/1ZcG9nxuN2

Trans students have been the targets of extreme attacks —including bills advanced by some of my GOP colleagues in the Education Committee. I hope this CDC report will help these politicians realize that their fearmongering has put the wellbeing of kids at risk.

It is heartbreaking that more than a quarter of trans students have attempted suicide and 40 percent have experienced bullying at school in the past year. 
https://t.co/eXtyNvcVjb

Dreamers are members of our community who have grown up and built their lives in our country. Ending DACA would rip families apart and hurt the economy.

Congress must create a path to citizenship instead of leaving Dreamers vulnerable to legal threats.
Today the 5th Circuit Court of Appeals is hearing arguments in a case brought by anti-immigrant extremists seeking to end DACA protections.
Oregon will get $37 million to inventory and then replace lead pipes.

Everyone should have drinking water that is free from lead. The @EPA’s new rule sets a strong standard for lead pipe removal and replacement, and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law will help support this work with $2.6 billion in funding.
I’m committed to working with my @HouseDemocrats colleagues to solve America's child care crisis.

Child care can cost as much as housing in many parts of the country. 

Families are getting on waitlists before their child is born. 

And providers often can’t afford to adequately pay their own staff. #ChildCareWeekofAction
Because of the partnerships among governments, schools, and industry, Oregon is well-positioned to benefit from legislation like the CHIPS and Science Act.

Thank you to @OBIOregon for inviting me to join the roadshow in Hillsboro to discuss workforce development and how federal investments are creating new opportunities for economic growth. https://t.co/wcmuxCsvaJ

Investing in child care is good economic policy. Access to affordable child care helps families save money on child care costs and allows parents to advance in their careers—increasing family earnings even after their children are grown.

Project 2025 would gut reproductive rights, ban overtime pay, and eliminate the Department of Education.
 
I joined @RepDanGoldman and some colleagues for a discussion on Project 2025’s authoritarian plan to reshape America.

This #MentalIllnessAwarenessWeek is a good reminder to check in with your loved ones. 

To learn more about the risk factors and warning signs of mental health conditions, visit: https://t.co/1UPFTHd6G2
Today we mourn the innocent lives lost and commit ourselves to continue to strive for peace in the Middle East until Israelis and Palestinians can live side by side in safety, security, and dignity.
We should proceed with determination to work with our regional partners and global allies to halt the violence and deter a wider war.
As Iran and its proxies continue to attack Israel, we must stand in defense of our ally and against the threat that Iran poses to the stability of the region.

I continue to call for a negotiated bilateral ceasefire that includes immediate return of the hostages, the expeditious delivery of humanitarian aid, and movement of the region toward sustainable peace.

The ensuing war has claimed the lives of tens of thousands of Palestinians and left Gaza in shambles. At the same time, thousands of Israelis have been displaced and the country continues to live with the threat of terrorist attacks by Hamas and Hezbollah.
One year ago today Hamas waged a brutal attack on Israel. Terrorists killed more than 1,200 innocent people and took 240 hostages, nearly 100 of whom remain in Gaza.
I’ll continue to work with my colleagues on the Education Committee to advance the policies and resources needed to strengthen public education.
It’s World Teachers’ Day, a good time to thank all the hardworking educators in Oregon and across the country who help students reach their full potential.

Oregon: October 15 is the deadline to register to vote in November’s general election! If you’ve already registered, it’s a good time to check that your address and other information is up to date.

https://t.co/SFQfoKBPLb

Interactive activities like this help keep students engaged while giving them experience they need to thrive in their future careers. As a Co-Chair of the bipartisan Career & Technical Education (CTE) Caucus, I’ll continue to support PCC OMIC Training Center & other CTE programs.

We toured the mobile welding truck and met with students who were participating in a simulation game where they got to run their own manufacturing companies and hone their teamwork and problem-solving skills.
It was great to meet with leaders and students at @PortlandCC and Oregon Manufacturing Innovation Center (OMIC) in Columbia County. https://t.co/bvkUHYfq9P

The climate crisis is causing more destructive and more frequent natural disasters, & tragically many Americans have experienced this firsthand in recent years. 

We must continue investing in clean energy & climate resilience to save lives & limit future damage to communities.
L'Shanah Tovah! This year’s high holiday season falls during a challenging time. I hope everyone observing Rosh Hashanah has a sweet and peaceful new year.

Instead of engaging in racist and xenophobic rhetoric, we should focus on real solutions—like the need to update the Low-Income Housing Tax Credit. The House already passed the bipartisanship update; Senate Republicans need to stop blocking it.

The lack of affordable housing comes up in many conversations I have in NW Oregon. 

Contrary to what some extremist politicians claim, immigration is not a cause of our affordable housing shortage.

Along with staying up to date with vaccinations, testing can help protect you and your loved ones from COVID-19. 

You can order 4 free at-home COVID tests by visiting: https://t.co/JgymMabc9C

LGBTQI+ history is American history, and it shouldn’t be erased from school curriculum.

As a Vice Chair of the @EqualityCaucus and a senior member of @EdWorkforceDems, I'll always stand up against censorship and fearmongering from extremist politicians. #LGBTQIHistoryMonth

For loans in default, Fresh Start allows borrowers to access federal student aid programs and removes the record of default from your credit report. 

For more information, visit: https://t.co/wnb7ivlya1
Student loan borrowers: the Education Department extended the deadline for the Fresh Start program, but just until tomorrow.

Americans rely on the U.S. Post Office for voting, Social Security checks, prescription drugs, and more. 

I urge USPS management and @APWUnational to negotiate in good faith and deliver a contract that’s needed for a reliable USPS.

SNAP recipients will see their benefits increase in October after the latest cost of living adjustment. I’m committed to strengthening SNAP and other anti-hunger programs to better meet the needs of people struggling to put food on the table.
I introduced a pair of bills with @WhipKClark and my House Democratic  colleagues to invest in child care facilities and the child care workforce. https://t.co/DxOelyUCVG
Expanding access to quality child care benefits everyone, but many child care providers can’t afford the building improvements or additional staff needed to serve more children and families.

This rock was painted in memory of Marna, who lost her life to breast cancer. It now has a home in my DC office to increase awareness of this devastating cancer. I encourage all who are at risk to consult with their doctor and get screened at the appropriate time. https://t.co/DKRphhMvjx
National Public Lands Day is a great time to celebrate the beautiful public lands and waters of our country and recommit to preserving these natural spaces for future generations.
As National Estuary Week comes to close, I encourage you to learn more about these incredible places. https://t.co/ZELMJPIfne
Estuaries are among the most productive ecosystems in the world. They help provide habitat, filter water, and protect coastal communities from flooding and storms.
It is deeply frustrating that many of my colleagues continue to demonize asylum seekers and immigrants instead of working on meaningful, humane immigration reform.

Recently I heard from immigration advocates and leaders about how the lack of support and resources is leaving asylum seekers unable to meet their basic needs, including shelter.
https://t.co/gZJqdVvzwl

Great news! @NOAA’s Pacific Marine Environmental Laboratory, which conducts valuable ocean research and monitoring, is receiving $3.9 million from the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law to improve observation and laboratory equipment.

One year ago this week the Biden-Harris Administration created the White House Office of Gun Violence Prevention to address the scourge of gun violence in our country. Learn more about their work and the progress here: https://t.co/S4FYJ5IP1L

Last week I went to the Library of Congress to pick out books for students at @PPSConnect’s Robert Gray Middle School and Markham Elementary School! These books come from the @librarycongress Surplus Books Program. https://t.co/AbqQSAXsE4

Central City Concern’s CHIERS van helped many people reach sobering centers in Portland. This bipartisan legislation will build on that model to create new transportation programs in Oregon and across the country. https://t.co/PDnYaCA8yv
People who are intoxicated or in danger of overdosing need a safe way to access care. Lack of transportation shouldn’t be a barrier to getting help.
September is #RecoveryMonth, when we stand with and support people in recovery and raise awareness about the lives that have been lost to overdose. https://t.co/B9Kj5fSZyh
I’m grateful that the House passed this legislation and I will continue advocating with Rep. Kean for the Senate to schedule a vote on the bill.

The bipartisan ASCEND Act is a commonsense solution to help researchers benefit from the vast, high-quality data available from commercial satellites to better understand climate change, natural disasters, and earth sciences. https://t.co/MArehv5t8i
It was a pleasure to meet with the Oregon Association of Nurseries to discuss workforce, climate change, horticulture, and specialty crops. https://t.co/pPOEqNJQhj
I’m grateful to partner with Whip Clark to introduce legislation that will provide funding to improve and build facilities to help meet the demand for affordable, accessible child care.

Child care is infrastructure and an important investment for children, families, and the economy. The ongoing hurdles child care providers and families face are limiting economic growth, threatening employers and small businesses, and holding back working families.
